'''C·G·P·格雷'''（{{lang-en|CGP Grey}}），本名'''科林·格雷戈里·帕爾默·格雷'''（{{lang|en|Colin Gregory Palmer Grey}}）<ref>{{cite news|author1=Bailey Johnson|title=The difference between England, Great Britain and the United Kingdom - CBS News|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/the-difference-between-england-great-britain-and-the-united-kingdom/|accessdate=2016-01-27|agency=CBS News|archive-date=2018-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123133019/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/the-difference-between-england-great-britain-and-the-united-kingdom/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=Mallika Rao|title='10 Misconceptions Debunked': CGP Grey Tackles Knuckle-Cracking, Spider-Eating, And The Many Words For Snow (VIDEO)|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/01/25/10-misconceptions-debunked_n_1231651.html|accessdate=2016-01-27|agency=The Huffington Post|archive-date=2015-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402003134/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/01/25/10-misconceptions-debunked_n_1231651.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是一名在[[YouTube|YouTube]]上的{{le|教育娛樂|Educational entertainment}}影片製作者。他擁有[[美國公民|美國]]和{{le|愛爾蘭國籍法|Irish nationality law|愛爾蘭}}雙國籍<ref>{{cite twitter|user=cgpgrey|number=250169830043443200|author=CGP Grey|title=CGP Grey on 24 September 2012.|date=24 Sep 2012}}</ref>。他的頻道主要內容為說明短片，主題包括政治、地理、經濟和英國文化。頻道第一段流行的影片是解釋[[英倫諸島|英倫諸島的名稱]]<ref>{{cite web|author=C. G. P. Grey|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CQ3qWgH4B0|title=One Year & 100,000 Subscribers Later (Thank You!)|publisher=YouTube|work=CGPGrey|date=January 30, 2012|accessdate=January 20, 2013|archive-date=2016-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101155552/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CQ3qWgH4B0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此後，格雷的短片便被受關注，[[商業內幕|商業內幕]]、[[哈芬登郵報|哈芬登郵報]]、[[福布斯|福布斯]]和[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]等媒體皆有報導<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|last=Kasanoff|first=Bruce|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/brucekasanoff/2014/08/18/if-humans-need-not-apply-will-all-our-jobs-disappear/|title=If 'Humans Need Not Apply,' Will All Our Jobs Disappear?|publisher=''Forbes''|date=August 18, 2014|accessdate=August 21, 2014|archive-date=2016-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120095404/http://www.forbes.com/sites/brucekasanoff/2014/08/18/if-humans-need-not-apply-will-all-our-jobs-disappear/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=HuffPostUK>{{cite web |url = http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/08/18/robots-steal-your-job_n_5687541.html |title = Why Robots Will Steal Your Job, In One 15 Minute Video |publisher = ''Huffington Post UK'' |date = August 18, 2014 |accessdate = August 23, 2014 |archive-date = 2017-09-17 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170917171516/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2014/08/18/robots-steal-your-job_n_5687541.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name=BusinessInsider>{{cite web |last = Love |first = Dylan |url = http://www.businessinsider.com/humans-need-not-apply-video-2014-8 |title = Not Even Doctors And Lawyers Are Safe From Machines Taking Their Jobs |publisher = ''Business Insider'' |date = August 13, 2014 |accessdate = August 23, 2014 |archive-date = 2014-08-26 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140826113234/http://www.businessinsider.com/humans-need-not-apply-video-2014-8 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name=Pope>{{cite web|author=Aaron Blake|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-fix/wp/2013/02/25/why-is-the-pope-always-so-old-video/|title=Why is the pope always so old? (Video)|publisher=''Washington Post''|date=February 25, 2013|accessdate=March 4, 2013|archive-date=2014-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018005448/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-fix/wp/2013/02/25/why-is-the-pope-always-so-old-video/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

